recipe.label: Fried Circassian cheese with a Middle-East
ingredientLines: * a few slice of fresh circassian cheese, mozzarella, edam or gouda
* 1.5 tb of circassian spice mixture, or: 2 tsp sweet paprika, 1 tsp
pepper, a pinch of salt, 1 tb ground walnut or almond
* 1 egg plus 1 tsp of water, mixed
* 3 large leaf of salad, or 1/4 of a head of lettuce
* 1/2 of a large english cucumber, or 1 regular sized cucumber
* 1/2 of a red, yellow, or orange pepper
* 1-2 tb of za'atar spice mixture, or a spice mixture of your choice
(herbe de provence would also go well in here)
* 1 tb champagne vinegar, or white wine vinegar
* a pinch of salt, to taste
